  "user_line_comments": {
    "830": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nPerforms the tape load operation by calling the Kernal tape read block routine\n($F4A5). After reading, it checks the Kernal I/O status word ($90). If any\nerror status bits (excluding bit 6) are set, it branches to the error handler.\n\nInputs:  ptr_load_addr_lo/ptr_load_addr_hi ($C3/$C4) - Tape load address\nOutputs: None\nSide Effects: Reads tape block into memory. If read fails, triggers error_reset.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "843": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nHandles tape loading/verification errors.\nDecrements the cartridge magic byte ($8004) to invalidate any cartridge\nautostart, then triggers a standard Kernal system reset to safely reboot the C64.\n\nInputs:  None\nOutputs: None (does not return)\nSide Effects: Cartridge magic byte at $8004 is decremented; system reboots.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "849": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nRestores the CHROUT vector, loads the game from tape, then decrypts and\nrelocates it in two passes:\n  Pass 1: $5000-$8FFF → $8000-$BFFF  (64 pages, key: SBC $58 / EOR $53)\n  Pass 2: $0800-$4FFF → $1000-$57FF  (72 pages, key: SBC $52 / EOR $4F)\nAfter decryption, sets the IRQ vector to $9853 and jumps to start_game.\nDoes not return (no RTS).\n\nInputs:       None\nOutputs:      None (no RTS — jumps to start_game)\nSide Effects: Tape loaded into $0800-$8FFF; game decrypted into $1000-$BFFF;\n              IRQ vector ($0314/$0315) set to $9853; interrupts re-enabled.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "881": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\ndecrypt 1",
    "896": "First decryption loop: decrypts $5000-$8FFF → $8000-$BFFF (64 pages, downwards)",
    "920": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\ndecrypt 2",
    "928": "Second decryption loop: decrypts $0800-$4FFF → $1000-$57FF (72 pages, downwards)",
    "970": "Initialize loader:\nDisable screen display and normal function keys.\nMap $0328 (STOP vector) to custom handler.",
    "1004": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nIntercepts the standard KERNAL CHROUT character output routine. If the trigger\nflag at $03FF is non-zero, it routes execution to initialize and run the tape loader.\nOtherwise, it forwards the call to the original KERNAL CHROUT routine.\n\nInputs:  loader_trigger_flag ($03FF) - Trigger flag\nOutputs: None\nSide Effects: Starts the loader if trigger is set; otherwise prints character.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-",
    "1012": "=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-\nVerifies that the loading and decryption completed without any Kernal status\nerrors. If no errors are present, it jumps to the decrypted game's entry point\nat $1800. Otherwise, it jumps to the error reset handler.\n\nInputs:  status_word ($90) - Kernal I/O status word\nOutputs: None (does not return)\nSide Effects: Jumps to game entry point at $1800 on success, or reboots on error.\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-"
  },
